GENERAL ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM/CHEMICAL-SPECIFIC PREVENTION STEPS

PGV has implemented a comprehensive program known as Process Safety Management (PSM) to prevent accidental releases of highly hazardous chemicals.  PSM is an integral part of working safely here at PGV.  PSM ensures that proper safety information is in place; operating procedures are followed; chemical hazards are identified; employees and contractors are trained and qualified; equipment designs are appropriate to applicable standards; equipment replacements are like in kind; and critical equipment is properly inspected and maintained.  Some of the many, specific safety features to prevent a chemical accident include:

AÂ· Extensive safety information about the process available to employees;

AÂ· Written operating procedures that include emergency response actions;

AÂ· Comprehensive employee and contractor training programs to promote consistently safe work-practices;

AÂ· Maintenance programs to ensure ongoing equipment reliability - includes equipment testing and inspection;

AÂ· Compliance auditing to ensure standards are being followed;

AÂ· A safety procedure to review proposed plant modifications before they are implemented for possible hazards;

AÂ· Safety pre-qualification for all contractors;

AÂ· Safety reviews prior to start-up of our process; and,

AÂ· Safety procedures that control hazards during special operations such as welding and cutting.

